Task:
As a cloud engineer you deployed 
a pod and the pod is stuck in "pending state".
It means the pod has not been scheduled
to run in the nodes

# Solution:
1. check for the nodes status
Kubectle get nodes

2. secondly inspect the pods
Kubectl get pods
Kubectl describe  pod <podnamne>

3. check resources
By checking the pods yaml file to check
resources allocation

4. Check events
Kubectl get events

